# Mission plan

**Execution model:** Squad Leader orchestrates stages on separate agent lanes. Stage I (**debug-and-fix**) is always spawned. After a verified fix, the developer picks **code promotion** (**`new-plan`** with **`pr-plan`** population, then **`coding-session`** with `targetPlanPath`), **Ad-Hoc PRD only**, or **findings report only**. When the fix is not verified or blocked, the Squad Leader produces a **Debug session findings report** before dispatch resolution. Reuse plan-and-deliver planning and ship skills; do not duplicate ship-chain steps in this mission.

## Objectives

1. **Log-first diagnosis** — Bootstrap a debug worktree, prioritize log access and debug instrumentation before substantive code analysis.
2. **Fix loop** — Propose fixes with test scenarios; apply on developer approval; run automated tests and guided manual verification; loop on failure until fixed or blocked.
3. **Post-fix routing** — After a verified fix, the developer selects **exactly one** exit:
   - **Code promotion** — create a plan anchor (**`new-plan`** plus **`pr-plan`**) before spawning **`coding-session`** on the debug worktree, so deploy tests and additional written tests have a PR plan to update.
   - **Ad-Hoc PRD only** — spawn **`ad-hoc-prd`** to capture fix context without starting code promotion.
   - **Findings report only** — no planning, no **`coding-session`**; Squad Leader produces a **Debug session findings report** from child outputs.
4. **Reuse plan-and-deliver** — Downstream delivery delegates to existing R&D skills; this mission owns debug orchestration only.

### Ship chain inheritance (binding)

**Code promotion** delegates ship execution to plan-and-deliver **`coding-session`** — this mission does **not** duplicate ship-chain or review-cycle procedure. After PR creation on that path, the same inline **`pr-review`** / **`pr-review.mjs`** boundary applies per [plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc § Post-PR handoff](../plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc). Load [plan-and-deliver `pr-review/SKILL.md`](../plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-review/SKILL.md) from **`coding-session`** [Post-create-pr handoff gate](../plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#post-create-pr-handoff-gate) — do not substitute generic **`gh`** PR inspection.

**Repo rules ship inheritance (binding).** Detached **`coding-session`** lanes execute canonical plan-and-deliver repo-rules behavior — this wrapper does **not** duplicate reconcile or post-review rule-update steps. **Pre-PR:** [plan-and-deliver `coding-session/SKILL.md` § *Repo rules reconciliation (binding)*](../plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#repo-rules-reconciliation-binding) and [Repo rules reconciliation gate](../plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#repo-rules-reconciliation-gate). **Post-review:** when inline **`pr-review`** classifies **Rule-update required**, follow [Post-review repo rules handoff](../plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#post-review-repo-rules-handoff) after the disposition gate — see [plan-and-deliver `pr-review/SKILL.md`](../plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-review/SKILL.md).

**Parallel `hosting-repo-rules` fork (cross-ref only):** When product **`coding-session`** terminals carry **`repoRulesReconciliationStatus: pending`**, parent **`planner`** / **`phase-planner`** may fire-and-forget spawn **`hosting-repo-rules`** per canonical [plan-and-deliver `coding-session/SKILL.md` § *Spawner spawn-detection outputs*](../plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#spawner-spawn-detection-outputs) and [plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc §8 detached branches](../plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc). This wrapper inherits that contract — **no duplicate spawn prose here**.

**Dispatch display refresh (Squad Leader).** When dispatch scope is readable (opening command phrase or issue summary from the opening message), call MCP **`mission_control_update_dispatch_display`** with non-empty **`dispatchTitle`** (≤64 chars) and optional **`dispatchDescription`** / **`dispatchHoverDescription`** (≤512 chars). **Skip** when current dispatch chrome already matches. **Forbidden:** **`mission_control_update_lane_display`** to relabel **child** slots from the leader lane; hand-editing **`dispatch-tab.v1.json`**. See [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/9_display-metadata-authority.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/9_display-metadata-authority.mdc).

