## Protocol

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  A[Infer command] --> B[Collect issue context]
  B --> C[Spawn debug-and-fix]
  C --> D{Fix verified?}
  D -->|no / blocked| F[Debug session findings report]
  D -->|yes| E{Post-fix exit}
  E -->|Code promotion| G[Spawn new-plan + pr-plan]
  G --> H[Spawn coding-session with targetPlanPath]
  H --> I[Dispatch resolution]
  E -->|Ad-Hoc PRD only| J[Spawn ad-hoc-prd]
  J --> I
  E -->|Findings report only| F
  F --> I
```

### 1. Infer intent from the opening command phrase

- `type`: Branching logic.
- `intent`: Match the opening command to Debug and Fix mission behavior.
- `inputs`: Opening user message and `mission.yaml` command phrase inventory.
- `expected output`: Intent label `debug-and-fix` when the command phrase is `debug and fix`, matched case-insensitively.
- `next-step resolution`: If the command phrase matches, continue to step 2 (auto-advance). If it does not match or intent is ambiguous, USER_CHECKPOINT gate below.
- `branch predicates`:
  - Opening message starts with `debug and fix` (case-insensitive) → intent `debug-and-fix`.
  - Otherwise → invalid or unsupported command for this mission.
- `default/fallback behavior`: Open structured choice to confirm intent before continuing.

USER_CHECKPOINT — confirm mission intent when the opening command phrase does not match.
- `ordered actions`:
  1. Match `debug and fix` case-insensitively.
  2. When dispatch scope is readable from the opening message (command remainder), run **Dispatch display refresh** (above) — **skip** when current dispatch chrome already matches.
  3. Continue to step 2.

### 2. Collect issue context

- `type`: Branching logic.
- `intent`: Gather symptom, scope, and reproduction hints before spawning the debug agent.
- `inputs`: Opening user message remainder after `debug and fix`, current Sedea user context (`operationsUserId`).
- `expected output`: Structured handover: `issueSummary`, optional `reproductionSteps`, optional `logHints`, optional `repoPath`.
- `next-step resolution`: Continue to step 3 when `issueSummary` is non-empty (auto-advance).
- `ordered actions`:
  1. Remove the matched command prefix from the opening message.
  2. Treat remaining text as initial `issueSummary` when present.
  3. Collect missing **`issueSummary`** via structured choice when empty.
  4. Optionally collect **`reproductionSteps`**, **`logHints`**, and **`repoPath`** (default hosting repo root when omitted).
  5. When **`issueSummary`** improves the dispatch title, re-run **Dispatch display refresh** (§ above) — **skip** when current dispatch chrome already matches.
- `valid early-exit conditions`: Stop without spawn if the user declines to provide an issue summary.

USER_CHECKPOINT — provide issue summary before spawning the debug agent.

### 3. Debug and fix (spawned skill)

- `type`: Agent engagement and handover.
- `execution`: spawned.
- `intent`: Run log-first diagnosis, fix loop, and exit recommendation on a child lane.
- `target agent role`: Debug and Fix agent.
- `assigned skill`: [`skills/debug-and-fix/SKILL.md`](skills/debug-and-fix/SKILL.md).
- `required rule context`: Sedea center always-apply rules, [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/20_efficient-pr-shipping.mdc`](../../rules/20_efficient-pr-shipping.mdc), [`.sedea/centers/sedea/skills/worktree-setup/SKILL.md`](../../../sedea/skills/worktree-setup/SKILL.md), [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc`](../../../sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc) § *Attach worktree to VS Code workspace*, [`.cursor/rules/dot-sedea.mdc`](.cursor/rules/dot-sedea.mdc), [`.cursor/rules/sedea-debug-logging-settings.mdc`](.cursor/rules/sedea-debug-logging-settings.mdc) — **hosting-repo authored** when present (like dot-sedea); create via cursor-center alignment when missing. Deprecated [`worktree-bootstrap/SKILL.md`](../plan-and-deliver/skills/worktree-bootstrap/SKILL.md) is **exception-only inline retry** when center setup fails — not normative warm-up. Submodule Node toolchain (`fnm use`) is per dot-sedea appendix, not a separate hosting warmUp file.
- `inputs`: `issueSummary`, `reproductionSteps`, `logHints`, `repoPath`, `operationsUserId` from step 2.
- `spawn run-request fields`:
  - `inputs` — validated fields above.
  - `warmUpRules` — skill frontmatter defaults plus mission context paths when needed.
  - `initiatingPrompt` — protocol step, symptom, and any user decisions from step 2.
- `expected output`: Child **`AGENT_RESULT_RESPONSE_V1`** with `outputs.fixStatus`, `outputs.worktreePath`, `outputs.worktreeName`, `outputs.hostingRoot`, `outputs.exitRecommendation` (`code-promotion` | `ad-hoc-prd` | `findings-report-only` | `blocked`), `outputs.fixSummary`, `outputs.testEvidence`.
- `next-step resolution`: On `fixStatus: verified`, continue to step 4 (auto-advance). On `blocked` or `failed`, continue to step 6 (debug session findings report). On `partial`, USER_CHECKPOINT gate below.
- **Agent session closure**: Child emits one parseable **`AGENT_RESULT_RESPONSE_V1`** line per skill **`## Completion (spawned)`**. Squad Leader waits for host delivery before continuing (**#external-wait**).

USER_CHECKPOINT — pick next step when debug child reports partial status.
- **Dispatch resolution**: Remains Squad Leader responsibility — child does not emit **`MC_DISPATCH_RESOLVED_V1`**.

### 4. Post-fix exit selection

- `type`: Branching logic.
- `intent`: Developer picks **exactly one** post-fix path when `outputs.fixStatus` is `verified`.
- `inputs`: Child `outputs.exitRecommendation`, `outputs.fixSummary`, `outputs.testEvidence`, `outputs.worktreePath`, `outputs.worktreeName`, `outputs.hostingRoot`.
- `expected output`: Exit label `code-promotion`, `ad-hoc-prd`, or `findings-report-only`.
- `next-step resolution`:
  - `code-promotion` → step 5.
  - `ad-hoc-prd` → step 5c.
  - `findings-report-only` → step 6.
- `branch predicates`:
  - Developer selects code promotion → step 5 (even when recommendation differs — developer override allowed with structured choice).
  - Developer selects Ad-Hoc PRD only → step 5c.
  - Developer selects findings report only → step 6.
- `default/fallback behavior`: Present **`exitRecommendation`** as the suggested default in modal labels; require explicit pick — one path mandatory.

USER_CHECKPOINT — pick exactly one post-fix exit path after a verified fix.

### 5. Create PR plan anchor (spawned planning handoff — code-promotion path only)

- `type`: Agent engagement and handover.
- `execution`: spawned.
- `intent`: Create the PR plan anchor required before code promotion, so `coding-session` receives `targetPlanPath` and can update deploy-test and written-test sections during ship.
- `target agent role`: Debug promotion planning agent (plan-and-deliver).
- `assigned skill`: [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/new-plan/SKILL.md`](../plan-and-deliver/skills/new-plan/SKILL.md), followed by **`pr-plan`** population per [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-plan/SKILL.md`](../plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-plan/SKILL.md).
- `inputs`: `mode: "standalone"`, `requestedPlanKind: "pr-plan"`, `upstreamSkill: "debug-and-fix"`, `operationsUserId`, and a debug handover seed containing child `outputs.fixSummary`, `outputs.testEvidence`, `outputs.worktreePath`, `outputs.worktreeName`, and `outputs.hostingRoot`. Root plan parent is resolved inside **`new-plan`** (sidecar **`parent: null`**) — **`new-plan`** frontmatter has no `parent` spawn key. When this step spawns a skill whose frontmatter declares **`parent`** as **`type: string`** (for example **`planner`** on other paths), emit **`"parent": "null"`** in spawn JSON for standalone root plans — **never** JSON `null`. See **`plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md`** § *Universal spawn preflight* row **1b**.
- `spawn run-request fields`: `inputs`, `warmUpRules` per target skill frontmatter, `laneRules` when required by the planning skill manifest, and `initiatingPrompt` with debug handover plus the approved post-fix exit.
- `pr-plan standalone exception`: Debug fixes do not necessarily originate from an approved parent **`### PR list`**. This mission explicitly permits a standalone **`pr-plan`** population handoff after **`new-plan`** creates the target plan; the handoff must pass `targetPlanPath`, `targetPlanSlug`, and the debug handover seed. If **`pr-plan`** cannot populate without parent topology, stop and use structured choice to revise the plan anchor, create the missing parent planning context, or switch exits — do not spawn **`coding-session`** without a PR plan.
- `expected output`: Child terminal or aggregate output with `outputs.targetPlanPath`, `outputs.targetPlanSlug`, `outputs.readyForImplementation: true`, and any `outputs.remainingTasks` from **`new-plan`** / **`pr-plan`**.
- `next-step resolution`: Continue to step 5b only after a readable PR plan path/slug exists and the PR plan is approved as ready for implementation. If the planning child reports unresolved plan target, missing parent topology that blocks standalone population, or approval gaps, USER_CHECKPOINT gate below.
- **Agent session closure** and **Dispatch resolution**: Same as step 3 — child terminal only; Squad Leader continues protocol.

USER_CHECKPOINT — revise planning anchor, retry, or switch exits when PR plan creation is blocked.

### 5b. Code promotion (spawned skill)

- `type`: Agent engagement and handover.
- `execution`: spawned.
- `intent`: Run plan-and-deliver ship chain from an already-modified debug worktree after PR plan creation.
- `target agent role`: Coding session agent (plan-and-deliver).
- `assigned skill`: [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md`](../plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md).
- `inputs`: `repoPath` / `outputs.hostingRoot`, existing `outputs.worktreePath` and `outputs.worktreeName` from debug child (worktree already created and modified), `developerApprovedImplementation: true`, `upstreamSkill: debug-and-fix`, required `targetPlanPath` and `targetPlanSlug` from step 5, plus `planningHandoffMode: "sections-1-4-complete"` and `planningHandoffApproved: true` when supplied by the **`pr-plan`** handoff.
- `spawn run-request fields`: `inputs`, `laneRules` / `warmUpRules` per **`coding-session`** frontmatter, and `initiatingPrompt` — state that implementation is complete on the debug worktree and ship chain starts at cut-point / commit per **`coding-session`** authority.
- `expected output`: Child terminal after ship chain milestones per **`coding-session`** **`## Completion (spawned)`** / inline ship skills.
- `next-step resolution`: Continue to step 7 after child terminal or when developer selects an external-wait resume option per skill gates.
- **Note:** Ship steps (commit, Local test deploy-walk, pre-pr-review, create-pr, pr-review, merge, post-merge cleanup, Staging test deploy-walk, After deploy deploy-walk, plan-reconcile) are **owned by `coding-session`** — do not duplicate procedure here. For **tapcart-push** and **tapcart-merchant-dashboard**, **`create-pr`** uses **outsider handoff** (no Sedea `gh pr create`) per **`create-pr/SKILL.md`** § *Outsider repos*.

### 5c. Create Ad-Hoc PRD (spawned skill — Ad-Hoc PRD path only)

- `type`: Agent engagement and handover.
- `execution`: spawned.
- `intent`: Capture fix context as an Ad-Hoc PRD when the developer wants product-context documentation instead of immediate code promotion.
- `target agent role`: Ad-Hoc PRD creator (plan-and-deliver).
- `assigned skill`: [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/ad-hoc-prd/SKILL.md`](../plan-and-deliver/skills/ad-hoc-prd/SKILL.md).
- `inputs`: `createIntent: true`, `title` from fix summary, `details` from child `outputs.fixSummary`, `operationsUserId`, optional `sourceSummary` referencing debug dispatch and test evidence.
- `spawn run-request fields`: `inputs`, `warmUpRules` per target skill frontmatter, `initiatingPrompt` with debug handover and the selected Ad-Hoc PRD-only exit.
- `expected output`: Child terminal with `outputs.adHocPrdPath`, `outputs.developerApprovedPrd` after PRD approval flow inside skill.
- `next-step resolution`: Continue to step 7 after child terminal; do not spawn **`coding-session`** from this branch unless the developer later selects code promotion and step 5 creates a PR plan anchor.
- **Agent session closure** and **Dispatch resolution**: Same as step 3 — child terminal only; Squad Leader continues protocol.

### 6. Debug session findings report

- `type`: Finish/stop logic.
- `intent`: Summarize debug session outcomes when fix is **not** verified, **blocked**, or the developer chose **findings report only** at step 4.
- `inputs`: All child terminal outputs from step 3 (`fixSummary`, `testEvidence`, `fixStatus`, worktree paths), and any user decisions from step 4 when applicable.
- `expected output`: Structured findings recap in **`display.markdown`** — symptom, diagnosis, fix attempts, test evidence, worktree state, and recommended follow-up. No downstream spawn.
- `next-step resolution`: Continue to step 7.
- `terminal vs resumable`: Resumable — dispatch remains active until step 7.

### 7. Dispatch resolution

USER_CHECKPOINT — approve dispatch resolution after findings report or code-promotion chain completes.

- `type`: Finish/stop logic.
- `intent`: Propose dispatch closure after findings report or code-promotion chain completes.
- `inputs`: All child terminal outputs, selected exit path, findings report from step 6 when applicable, any external-wait resume selection state.
- `expected output`: Squad Leader recap and **`MC_DISPATCH_RESOLVED_V1`** when user signals done.
- `next-step resolution`: Terminal when user accepts resolution or continues from resolution card per [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/4_mission.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/4_mission.mdc) § *Dispatch resolution*.
- `terminal vs resumable`: **`resolved`** when code-promotion chain completed or findings report delivered; **`partial`** when fix verified but ship pending external action; **`aborted`** / **`abandoned`** on user stop or unrecoverable block.
